23things_challengeme_xs.png Technical data wrangling skills are fast becoming a new form of data literacy.  The four Carpentry concepts listed below have really taken off over the past couple of years.

The “one hour a week” model for 23 Things doesn’t allow enough time to do any of the Carpentry modules since most of them need at least several hours to complete, but here’s a chance for you to find out what all the Carpentry buzz is about.

Have a look at this Environmental scan (Links to an external site.)Links to an external site. of courses offering data skills. Then choose one Carpentry to explore in depth or browse over them all:

    Data Carpentry (Links to an external site.)Links to an external site.
    Library Carpentry (Links to an external site.)Links to an external site.
    Software Carpentry (Links to an external site.)Links to an external site.
    Author Carpentry (Links to an external site.)Links to an external site.

We will get more hands-on with Carpentry in Thing 21.
